== COI violation ==

Hi, I've reverted all of your edits across the pages you've worked on, under our [[VRCWiki:Conflicts_of_interest]] policy. The policy says you should not directly edit content you are personally or professionally involved with, since it's hard to stay neutral about a subject you're close to.

This isn't a judgment of your intentions, and you're still welcome to contribute. If there are changes you'd like to see on any of these pages, please post them on the relevant article's talk page and explain what you think should be updated and why. Another editor can then review the suggestion and make the change if it fits our guidelines. It also helps to declare your connection to the subject on your user page so other editors have the full context.

When you have a moment, it's worth reading through [[VRCWiki:How_to_Contribute]] and the [[VRCWiki:Contributor_hub]], along with our other policies and guidelines, so you know what to expect going forward. If you'd prefer to talk it through, you're welcome to join the wiki Discord at https://wiki.vrchat.com/discord, where editors are happy to help and answer questions.

